The two principal null directions of  Petrov type D space-times determine two geodesic and shear free null congruences with tangent vectors $l^a$ and $n^a$. For that reason two null electromagnetic fields with principal null directions $l^a$ and $n^a$  exist in type D space-times, such that the only non-vanishing Maxwell scalars are $\phi_2$ and $\phi_0$, respectively. This should not be confused with the case that a single null field is expressed in terms $\phi_2$ or $\phi_0$ by transformation of spin basis. The two null fields in type D space-times exist independently and simultaneously.

